English:
Supply chain: The factor “supply chain” which carries a weight of 30% in the total award criteria, with a maximum of 30 points.
The “supply chain” is understood as the supply circuit involving a number of economic operators responsible for the production, manufacturing and marketing of the products (food). The scoring algorithm for the “supply chain” evaluation factor will be inversely proportional, meaning that a smaller number of economic operators involved in the supply chain will receive a higher score.
Note: To obtain the corresponding score, economic operators must submit documents with the offer confirming direct delivery from the producer or the involvement of a single economic operator in the supply chain. – for direct deliveries (the bidder is the original producer) the maximum score of 30 points is awarded;
– for deliveries with a single economic operator involved in the supply chain (intermediary) – 20 points are awarded;
– for deliveries with two economic operators involved in the supply chain (intermediary) – 10 points are awarded;
– for three or more economic operators involved in the supply chain – no points are awarded.

