Lan?ul de aprovizionare: Componenta tehnic?
„Lan?ul de aprovizionare” La, cu o valoare de 30 de puncte din totalul de 100 de puncte ?i cu o pondere de 30 % din totalul criteriului de atribuire, se va acorda dup? cum urmeaz?:, Algoritm de calcul: 
PLa(n) = [(La-Lamin)/(Lamax-Lamin)]*30 
Unde: PLa(n): punctajul ob?inut de c?tre Oferta “n” pentru factorul Lantul de aprovizionare; 
La – num?rul de repere livrate direct (de la produc?torul original la consumatorul final); 
Lamin - num?rul repere livrate direct (de la produc?torul original la consumatorul final) minim ofertat; 
Lamax - num?rul repere livrate direct (de la produc?torul original la consumatorul final) maxim ofertat; 

Lan? de aprovizionare scurt se în?elege rela?ia direct? dintre produc?tor ?i consumator, între care nu poate exista mai mul?i intermediari, unde:
a) produc?torul este persoana fizic? sau juridic? care produce bunurile ofertate.
c) consumatorul este utilizatorul final;
d) intermediar este orice distribuitor/depozitar/comerciant care asigur? furnizarea produselor de la produc?tor la consumator.

Ofertantul î?i va asuma procentul bunurilor/materialelor pentru care are calitatea de produc?tor printr-o declara?ie pe propria r?spundere. 
Ofertantul va prezenta documente/proceduri de lucru prin care demonstreaz? existen?a unei strategii de management asociate sistemelor informatice prin care se asigur? gestiunea lan?ului de aprovizionare conform nivelului ofertat.

English:
Supply Chain: Technical Component
"Supply Chain" La, with a value of 30 points out of a total of 100 points and a weight of 30% of the total award criteria, shall be awarded as follows:, Calculation algorithm:
PLa(n) = [(La?Lamin)/(Lamax?Lamin)]*30
Where: PLa(n): the score obtained by Offer "n" for the Supply Chain factor;
La – the number of items delivered directly (from the original producer to the final consumer);
Lamin – the minimum number of items delivered directly (from the original producer to the final consumer) offered;
Lamax – the maximum number of items delivered directly (from the original producer to the final consumer) offered;

A short supply chain is understood as the direct relationship between producer and consumer, where no additional intermediaries may exist, where:
a) the producer is the natural or legal person who manufactures the offered goods;
c) the consumer is the end?user;
d) an intermediary is any distributor/warehouseman/trader who ensures the provision of products from the producer to the consumer.

The tenderer shall assume the percentage of goods/materials for which it has the status of producer by a self?declaration.
The tenderer shall present documents/work procedures that demonstrate the existence of a management strategy linked to the IT systems that ensure supply?chain management in accordance with the offered level.

